<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1436,736,929]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,777,803]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[719,743,778,803]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles on rear shield margin, directed posteriorly; empodium entire; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae; opisthosoma with one ridge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1436,736,929]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
This genus consists of 2 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[637,885,861,887]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[743,801,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species has been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
